basically, in disaster.

00:23:10.620 --> 00:23:14.230
And so Dave [? Herman ?] who
I'll speak for a little bit

00:23:14.230 --> 00:23:16.250
here, tends to talk about
the layers of an onion

00:23:16.250 --> 00:23:19.930
where you start with a
small group of people

00:23:19.930 --> 00:23:23.560
and then slowly grow
that and take input.

00:23:23.560 --> 00:23:27.330
But instead of shooting off
your proposal to a mailing list,

00:23:27.330 --> 00:23:29.440
actually seek out
people you think

00:23:29.440 --> 00:23:31.730
could have valuable
information, and then

00:23:31.730 --> 00:23:35.980
adjust the proposal as the
group of experts grows.

