00:41:03.720 --> 00:41:08.890
But maybe up a level,
that make sense."

00:41:08.890 --> 00:41:12.250
I don't know that there's
always a one-size-fits-all,

00:41:12.250 --> 00:41:12.890
go-to answer.

00:41:12.890 --> 00:41:15.710
There might be some
things we can't get down.

00:41:15.710 --> 00:41:18.780
But we should think about it.

00:41:18.780 --> 00:41:20.730
Sensor's is a really good one.

00:41:20.730 --> 00:41:22.020
Sensor's pretty low level.

00:41:22.020 --> 00:41:24.240
It's, I think, a hardware.

00:41:24.240 --> 00:41:28.770
But there are people
working on a standard, hey,

00:41:28.770 --> 00:41:31.460
there's how you do
sensors-- all of them.

00:41:31.460 --> 00:41:33.300
And it's actually pretty great.

00:41:33.300 --> 00:41:35.174
LYZA GARDNER: Divya's
shaking her head a bit.

00:41:36.122 --> 00:41:37.580
DIVYA MANNIAN:
First of all, I feel

00:41:37.580 --> 00:41:40.990
like me missing the point
