00:42:17.408 --> 00:42:20.400
configurations to a certain
version of the browser,

00:42:20.400 --> 00:42:21.950
and what do you do then?

00:42:21.950 --> 00:42:24.250
Do you forever support
this low level API?

00:42:24.250 --> 00:42:25.584
Or are you going to just say no?

00:42:25.584 --> 00:42:26.833
KENNETH CHRISTIANSEN: Exactly.

00:42:26.833 --> 00:42:28.520
Hardware is really,
really difficult,

00:42:28.520 --> 00:42:31.860
because if you take
something like a camera,

00:42:31.860 --> 00:42:34.590
the technology
changes every year.

00:42:34.590 --> 00:42:36.450
So if you make low
level primitives

00:42:36.450 --> 00:42:38.550
to how a camera works
today, well, those

00:42:38.550 --> 00:42:40.050
might not exist
two years from now

00:42:40.050 --> 00:42:43.631
and there might be new
low level primitives.

00:42:43.631 --> 00:42:45.630
