so many people who actually

01:14:41.300 --> 01:14:46.090
lived in Oakland felt so shut
out of the technology that

01:14:46.090 --> 01:14:49.630
was happening 30 miles
away in the Valley,

01:14:49.630 --> 01:14:51.190
eight miles away
in San Francisco,

01:14:51.190 --> 01:14:52.710
and coming to Oakland.

01:14:52.710 --> 01:14:56.660
And as much as everybody was
on their phone-- consuming

01:14:56.660 --> 01:14:59.760
technology, doing
gaming, doing messaging,

01:14:59.760 --> 01:15:01.930
doing e-commerce--
they had no idea

01:15:01.930 --> 01:15:04.300
that they could
really be consumers.

01:15:04.300 --> 01:15:07.640
And people were like,
"Gee, getting a job at UPS

01:15:07.640 --> 01:15:09.850
would be like a fantastic job.

01:15:09.850 --> 01:15:11.710
It has a lot of security."

01:15:11.710 --> 01:15:13.340
So we started Hack
the Hood because we

01:15:13.340 --> 01:15:17.230
wanted to grow a generation of
programmers and people working

01:15:17.230 --> 01:15:21.420
in other jobs in tech who
really were not shut out,

01:15:21.420 --> 01:15:24.390
who could be young people of
color from very low income

01:15:24.390 --> 01:15:24.970
families.

01:15:24.970 --> 01:15:28.050
So the kids that you saw on the
screen from our summer program

01:15:28.050 --> 01:15:30.430
in Oakland all
came from families

01:15:30.430 --> 01:15:34.030
that literally made less
than $18,000 a year.

01:15:34.030 --> 01:15:37.330
They were kids who started
out not doing any programming.

01:15:37.330 --> 01:15:40.260
Really avid users of
tech on their phone.

01:15:40.260 --> 01:15:44.280
And by the end of the
course, they not only all

01:15:44.280 --> 01:15:46.990
were doing web
development using weebly,

01:15:46.990 --> 01:15:52.730
but they were learning CSS,
HTML, starting to look at PHP.

01:15:52.730 --> 01:15:54.840
Here we are at the
end of the summer

01:15:54.840 --> 01:15:57.660
and we have kids who are
going to be taking classes

01:15:57.660 --> 01:16:00.580
in computer science, kids you're
going to start doing Android

01:16:00.580 --> 01:16:04.880
development in a workshop
with us with codepath.org.

01:16:04.880 --> 01:16:07.520
